        <num>CCP 4206</num>
        <heading>4206.  Termination of duties</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 4206.  Termination of duties
The undertutor is relieved of further duty and authority as undertutor when the minor reaches majority or is fully emancipated.  However, his liability for acts prior thereto shall not be affected.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=111935</p>
